15... h5 { Black is not joking about his intentions, White needs to be precise! } 16. Ng2!! Qxh3 (16... Qd8 { Suddenly it's Black's king that is in danger! } 17. fxg6 fxg6 18. e5! { very instructive method: to open the position to attack the enemy king in the center! } 18... Nxe5 19. Qc2 $40) 17. Rf3! Qxg4 18. Be2! { White sacrificed two pawns to stop Black's play on the h-file and create a counterattack! } { [%cal Gd1d6,Gc1f4] } 18... gxf5 (18... O-O-O 19. Bf4 $40 { [%cal Gd1d6,Gf3d3] }) (18... Ne5 19. Qxd6 Nxf3+ 20. Bxf3) 19. Re3! Qg5 20. exf5+ Ne7 21. Qxd6 { Such a turn of events! After few moves, it's White who has a deadly attack! } 21... Bc6 { [%csl Gg2][%cal Gg5g2] } 22. Re4! { [%cal Gc1g5] } 22... Qxg2+ (22... Nxf5 23. Qxc6+ bxc6 24. Bxg5 $18) 23. Kxg2 Bxe4+ 24. Kf2 Bxf5 25. Bg5 { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0


