[SetUp "1"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ As players repeat move after Qe2-Qd1, game ended in a draw, but in this position there is really Stockfish kinda tactic a human being in time trouble might easily miss. }
26... Qe2+ (26... Nd4! { works fine here too, but it's a bit more compliacated. } 27. Rb2 Qf3+ 28. Kh3 Qf1+ 29. Rg2 Nf3 30. Qb2 Ng1+ 31. Kh4) 27. Kg1 (27. Kh3 { leaves the white king exposed but the immediate win is still not obvious but instructive. } 27... Qf1+ 28. Kh4 Qf3 { [%cal Gf3h5] } 29. Kh3 h5! { with the instructive idea of including the black rook into the attack, White can not defend the king. } 30. Qb2 { to meet h4 with Qg2. } 30... Rh8 { but Black can change the move order and h4 will finish the game. } { [%csl Gh4][%cal Gh5h4] }) 27... Nd4!! (27... Qd1+ 28. Kg2 { 1/2-1/2 The game is a draw. }) 28. exd4 Qd1+! { a very important move to clear the e-file. } 29. Kg2 exd4 30. Qb2 Re8! { This is the whole point of opening up the e-line. } 31. Qb1 Qe2+ 32. Kg1 (32. Kh3 Qh5+ 33. Kg2 Re2+ { mates shortly. }) 32... Qd2! { and this is the last finesse, black wins. } { [%csl Ge1][%cal Ge8e1] } 1/2-1/2


