92. Nc4 Kc6! { The whole point of black's play is to prevent Ne7 idea by playin Ke6. Other bishop moves allow Ne5 and } (92... Bg5 93. Ne3 (93. Ne5 { and Black can not bring his king to e6. } 93... Bh4 94. Ng6 { [%csl Ge7][%cal Gg6e7] }) 93... Bf6?? (93... Kd6 { Again here it's still possibile to make a draw since Black can play Ke6 but in the game black blundered. }) 94. Nd5+ { 1-0 White wins. }) (92... Bh4 93. Ne3! { Due to fork on f5, black king can not reach e6-square. }) 93. Ne3 { [%cal Ge3f5,Gf5e7] } 93... Kd6! 94. Nf5+ Ke6 { White can not make progress. } 1-0


