{ As we might expect "all rook endgames are drawn" Black now played the move 37...Rb2 and the game ended in a draw, but due to his active king and the rook Black had a chance to win. }
37... Kg5! 38. Rxc5+ Kh4 { and White can not defend the position as Black creates a mating net and collects the white pawns on the kingside. } { [%csl Gg3][%cal Gh4g3] } 39. Kf1 Kg3 40. Rc3 Rf2+ 41. Ke1 Rxf3 42. Rxf3+ Kxf3 $19 *


