12. f4! { Since black bishop can not leave the a1-h8 diagonal due to Nxg7 tricks, he has to allow either 12.h3 after 11...Bf6 or take en passant. In the game he choses the third option. } 12... Bxd4+ (12... exf3 13. exf3 Bxh2+ (13... Nxh2 { and now white has many ways to win since the knight is trapped and he has a winning position. } { [%csl Gh2] } 14. Nc6 (14. Rf2 { [%cal Gf2e2] } 14... Bxd4 15. Qxe8+ Rxe8 16. Bxd4 { [%csl Gh2] }) 14... Bxa1 15. Rxd5) 14. Kh1 Qxe1 15. Rdxe1 { [%csl Rg4,Yh2] }) 13. Bxd4 { not only g7 is hanging but h3 is threatened as the knight has only the unfortunate f6 and h6 squres. } { [%csl Gg7,Gh3][%cal Gd4g7,Gh2h3] } 13... Qe6 14. Qh4! $18 { [%csl Yf6,Rd8,Rg5,Gg4][%cal Yg4f6,Rh4g5] } *


