12... Nd7 { Chess engines also like space advantage and domination theme! } 13. h6 g6 14. g4! { Not caring about the king safety as black is passive and can not create threats against white king with 14...Bh4. From now on it's clear that white is playing against black's minor pieces. This kind of long term weakening moves are more difficult for us, humans. } 14... O-O 15. Kf1 { [%csl Gg2][%cal Gf1g2] } 15... Rb8 16. Kg2 Nf6 17. Ra3 Ne8 18. a5 { White will further improve their pieces if black will not try to break free. } 18... b5 19. axb6 Rxb6 20. Bf3 Bf6 21. Ra2 Nc7 22. Ne2 Bd7 23. b3 Nb5 24. Bb2 Bxb2 25. Rxb2 Qf6 26. Ra2 { [%csl Ga6][%cal Gd1a1,Ga1a6] } 26... Nc7 27. c4 { Now domination really begins to take shape. } { [%csl Gd7,Gc7,Gd5,Gc4,Gg4,Gf4] } 27... Qh8 28. Re1 Qf6 29. Qc1! { White sacrifices a pawn to activate the knight. } { [%cal Gc1f4,Ge2g3,Gg3e4] } 29... Rxb3 30. Ng3 Qh4 31. Rh1 Qe7 32. Qa1 { [%cal Ga1g7] } 32... f6 33. Re1 Re3 34. Rae2 Rxe2+ 35. Rxe2 Qd8 36. Ne4 Bc8 37. Qb2 { [%cal Gb2b6] } 37... Rf7 38. Qb6 { [%csl Gd6][%cal Ge4d6,Gb6d6] } 38... Rd7 39. g5 { [%cal Ge4f6] } 39... fxg5 40. fxg5 { [%csl Gf6][%cal Ge4f6] } 40... Ne8 41. Qxd8 Rxd8 { Even though Black managed to exchange the queens domination continues. } 42. Rb2 Bf5 43. Ng3 Bc8 44. Kf2 Rd7 45. Rb8 Rc7 46. Bd1 Kf8 47. Ne4 Ke7 48. Ke3 a5 49. Nc3 Kf7 50. Kd2 Bh3 51. Ba4 Re7 52. Bc6 Nf6 { Black foresees all the possible losses decided to give up a pieces. One possible continuation was if black decided against 52...Nf6, } (52... Bf5 53. Nb5 { [%cal Gc6e8,Gb5d6] } 53... Bd7 54. Rb7 Bxc6 55. dxc6 Kf8 56. Kc3 Re3+ 57. Kb2 Re7 58. Ka3 $18 { [%cal Ga3a4,Ga4a5] }) 53. gxf6 Kxf6 54. Nb5 Ke5 55. Rg8 Bf1 56. Rg7 Kf6 57. Nxd6 Re2+ 58. Kd1 Rh2 59. Ne4+ Ke5 60. d6 Bh3 61. Rxh7 Bg4+ 62. Ke1 Bf5 63. Re7+ Kf4 64. h7 Rh1+ 65. Kf2 Rh2+ 66. Kg1 Rh6 67. Nxc5 g5 68. d7 Bxd7 69. Bxd7 Kf3 70. Bf5 Rh4 71. Re4 Rxh7 72. Ne6 Rh4 73. Nxg5+ Kg3 74. Rxh4 Kxh4 75. c5 Kxg5 76. c6 Kf6 77. c7 Kxf5 78. c8=Q+ Kf6 79. Kf2 a4 80. Ke3 a3 81. Ke4 a2 82. Qe8 a1=Q 83. Qh8+ Ke7 84. Qxa1 Kd6 85. Qc3 Ke6 86. Qd4 Kf7 87. Qd7+ Kf6 88. Kf4 Kg6 89. Qe7 Kh6 90. Kf5 Kh5 91. Qh7# { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0


