{ In Carlsbad Structure generally white aims to play on the queenside by creating a minority attack with b4-b5 to create a pawn weakness on black's camp meanwhile black tries to play on the kingside by using the e4-square. In this poisiton. Black seems to be pressing on each side of the board even though Stockfish assesses the position as equal after a move like 18.0-0. }
