1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6?! { In fact this logical move is what white is expecting, now white will get a better version of Rossolimo by transposing into a Grand-Prix! } (3... Nd4!) 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. f4! Bg7 6. d3 Nf6 7. Nf3 O-O 8. O-O { [%cal Rd1e1,Re1h4,Rf4f5,Rc1h6] } 8... b6 9. Qe1 Bg4 10. Ne5! { Knight on f3 is very important attacking piece! } 10... Qc7 11. Qh4 Be6 12. Nf3 h6 13. f5 g5 14. Nxg5! hxg5 15. Bxg5 Bc8 16. Rf3! Rd8 17. Bh6 Ne8 18. Bxg7 Nxg7 19. Rh3 f6 20. Qh7+ Kf7 21. Qg6+ Kg8 22. Rf1 e6 23. Qh7+ Kf7 24. fxe6+ Bxe6 25. Rh6 Qe5 26. Qg6+ Kg8 27. Rxf6 Qd4+ 28. Rf2 { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0


