{ In this game you'll find a similar attacking scheme by white, one of the most famous attacking games by former world champion Spassky. }
1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 d6 3. g3 { It's Closed Sicilian this time. If we understand the attacking patterns concerning this type of anti-Sicilians, we can usually play similar systems against Sicilian Defence. } 3... Nc6 4. Bg2 g6 5. d3 Bg7 6. f4 Nf6 7. Nf3 O-O 8. O-O Rb8 9. h3 b5 10. a3 a5 11. Be3 b4 12. axb4 axb4 13. Ne2 Bb7 14. b3 Ra8 15. Rc1 Ra2 16. g4 Qa8 17. Qe1 Qa6 18. Qf2 Na7 19. f5! { Here we go! } { [%cal Rf2h4,Rf3g5,Gf1f6] } 19... Nb5 20. fxg6 hxg6 21. Ng5 Na3 22. Qh4 Rc8 23. Rxf6 exf6 24. Qh7+ Kf8 25. Nxf7 Rxc2 26. Bh6 Rxc1+ 27. Nxc1 Kxf7 28. Qxg7+ Ke8 29. g5 f5 30. Qxg6+ Kd7 31. Qf7+ Kc6 32. exf5+ { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0


