31. Bxf7+! Rxf7 32. f4! { in order to play Rb8 withouth Bd8. } { [%csl Rg5] } (32. Qe6?? { but this is not the way which is in fact a blunder. Stockfish gives the winning line. } 32... Be7! { Realizing there is no follow-up to compansate his material deficit White resigned. }) 32... Qg4 33. Rb8+ Rf8 34. Qd5+ Kh7 35. Rxf8 { and there is no perpetual for Black. } 35... Qe2+ 36. Kh3 Qg4+ 37. Kh2 { [%cal Rg4e2,Bd5g2] } 37... h4 38. Qe4+ g6 39. Rxf6 { and there's still no perpetual White is winning. } 0-1


