39. Rxa4 Qxb4!! { A brilliant concept from the world champion: Queen sacrifice for a checkmating attack! } 40. Rxb4 Rxa1+ 41. Kh2 (41. Rb1 R8a2 42. Qd1 Rxb1 43. Qxb1 Rxf2 $19 { Black has an attack which will eventually cost White more material. }) 41... Kg7! { Another powerful move to avoid the checks from the back rank. } (41... R8a2? 42. Rb2 Rxb2 43. Qxb2 Rf1 44. Qb8+ { This is why Kg7 was important. } 44... Kh7 45. Qf4 $10 { [%cal Gf4h4] }) 42. Rb7 (42. Rb1 R8a2 43. Rb2 Rxb2 44. Qxb2 Rf1 $19) 42... Rf1! 43. Qxc6 Raa1 44. Rxf7+ { White is forced to give up material striving for perpetual check! } 44... Kxf7 45. Qxd5+ Kg7 46. Qe5+ Nf6 $19 { Black was winning even though game ended in a draw in the end. } 1/2-1/2


