35. Rc3?? { White is up an exchange for a pawn. Stockfish considers this position as balanced, but white's last move gives Black a surprising chance! } 35... Bd4! 36. Rf3 { Otherwise Black will play Rf6! } (36. Rc1 Rf6 $19 { Black would have a mating attack! }) (36. Rd3 Rxc4 37. Nxb6 Rc2+ 38. Kf1 Bf2 $19 { [%cal Gg4h2] }) 36... Ne5! 37. Rf4 Rxc4 38. Nxb6 Rc2+ (38... Rb4 { would also win as after } 39. Re7 Rxb6 40. Rxd4 Nc6 $19) 39. Kf1 (39. Kh1! { would be a better defence. }) 39... Be3! { This is the point of Gukesh's play and white's rook has no safe squares on the f-file, to protect the f2-square. } 40. a4 (40. Re4 Rf2+ 41. Ke1 (41. Kg1 Nf3+ 42. Kh1 Rh2#) 41... Nd3+ 42. Kd1 Rd2#) 40... Bxf4 $19 { Black is a pawn up with a dominant position and won shortly after. } 0-1


