18... Rf5!! { This is an amazing move and the only one to win. Black has various tactical motifs including Qf2 followed by Rg5 and Qxg3 mate or Nf7 to attack the white king or Qf6 to bring the queen closer to white king. The problem for White is his king is exposed and extra material is of no use. Since the position is very complicated i'll try to illustrate the general ideas to attak. } (18... Qe5 { This is how the game went, needing only a draw to quality to the next stage Black forced the perpetual check. } 19. b3 Qe6+ 20. Kh4 g5+ 21. Kxg5 Qg6+ 22. Kh4 Qxh6+ 23. Kg4 Qg6+ 24. Kh4 Qh6+ 25. Kg4 Qg6+ 26. Kh4 Qh6+ { 1/2-1/2 The game is a draw. }) 19. Rf1 (19. b3 { [%cal Ga1d4] } 19... Qf2! { [%csl Gg5][%cal Gf5g5] }) (19. Qg1 Qf6) 19... Nf7! 20. Rxf5 gxf5+ 21. Kf3 (21. Kh3 Qe3! 22. Kh2 Ne5! { and Black has perfect coordination for the mating attack. } 23. Bh3 Nf3+ 24. Kg2) 21... Qd2! { the only move that ends the game instantly, White is mated } { [%cal Gf7e5] } 22. exf5 Ne5+ 23. Ke4 Qd4# 1/2-1/2


