{ This game illustrates one of the ideas of pawn play in the center of Wade's Defence. }
1. Nf3 d6 2. d4 Bg4 3. Nbd2 Nd7 4. h3 Bh5 5. e3 (5. b3 e6 6. Bb2 Ngf6 7. e3 Be7 8. Be2 c6 9. O-O O-O 10. c4 a5 11. a3 Qb8 12. b4 b6 13. Bc3 axb4 14. axb4 Qb7 15. Qc2 Bg6 16. Bd3 Bxd3 17. Qxd3 { Koksal, E. - Dogan, N., 1/2-1/2, 7th Cesme Open A 2019, https://lichess.org/yZwv4MeI } { I tried to show the flexibility of Black's pawn play in extreme :) }) 5... Ngf6 6. Be2 e6 7. O-O d5 8. b3 a5 9. a3 Be7 10. Bb2 O-O 11. c4 c6 12. Bc3 Qb8 13. b4 axb4 14. Bxb4 Re8 15. Qc2 Qa7 16. Bxe7 Rxe7 17. Qb2 e5 18. dxe5 Nxe5 19. Rfc1 Rae8 20. c5 Ned7 21. Qb4 Ne4 22. Nb3 h6 23. Ra2 Bxf3 24. Bxf3 Ng5 25. Nd4 Nxf3+ 26. Nxf3 Ne5 27. Nxe5 Rxe5 28. Rb2 R8e7 29. Rd1 Re4 30. Rd4 Rxd4 31. exd4 Qa8 32. Rb1 Kf8 33. a4 Qa6 34. Qb6 Qxa4 35. Qd8+ Re8 36. Qd6+ Kg8 37. Rxb7 Qxd4 38. Qc7 Re1+ 39. Kh2 Qxf2 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


