16. Be3 { This game was played in the same event with the previous one and belongs to a different category than the GOTM but Carlsen shows how to fight against space advantage and heavy pieces can also be dominated. } 16... f4! { Preparing the operation! } 17. Bxf4 Bd7 18. Nd1 Rxf4!! { White's pieces look unorganized and Carlsen decides to take advantage of this fact in good fashion. } 19. Qxf4 Bh6 20. Qg3 Qf8 { Now white queen and the rook are having hard time to join the action. } 21. Ne3 Bf4 22. Qg2 Rc8 23. Rc3 Rxc3 24. bxc3 { Black should invade via queenside since white's army are idle on the kingside, as we can already guess. } 24... Qc8 25. c4 b5! { Black is trying to open up the queenside as soon as possible. } 26. axb6 axb6 27. Qg1 Qa8 28. Kf1 Qa2 29. Ng2 Qa1+ 30. Ne1 Qb2 31. Ng2 Qc1+ 32. Ne1 Qd2 33. Qg2 Kg7 { Carlsen is taking his time before further opening up the position with pawn levers. } 34. Rg1 Kf8 35. Qh1 e6 36. Rg3 exd5 37. exd5 (37. cxd5 b5 { [%cal Gb5b1] }) 37... Bf5 38. Rg1 Kf7 39. Rg3 Nd7 40. Rg5 Bxg5 41. hxg5 Ne5 { 0-1 Black wins. } { Black resigned as Black is still a pawn down but his position is falling apart. } { [%csl Gg5,Gc4][%cal Gd2c1,Ge5d3] } 0-1


