1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 d6 3. f4 Nc6 4. Nf3 g6 5. Bb5 { This is another way to develop the king's bishop. White will exchange the bishop for the knight to ruin black's structure and avoid Nd4. } 5... Bg7 6. Bxc6+ bxc6 7. d3 Nf6 8. O-O O-O 9. Qe1 { Similar attacking scheme by King! } { [%cal Ge1h4,Gf4f5,Gc1h6] } 9... Ne8 10. Qh4 f5 { black prevents f5 but weakens their king and the squares on the e-file } 11. Bd2 Nc7 12. Rae1! Ne6 13. exf5 gxf5 14. Rxe6! Bxe6 15. Ng5 Rf6 16. Qxh7+ Kf8 17. Nxe6+ Rxe6 18. Qxf5+ Rf6 19. Qg4 $18 d5 20. f5 Qd7 21. Na4 Qd6 22. Bf4 e5 23. Be3 d4 24. Bg5 Rf7 25. Qh4 Ke8 26. Qh5 Bf8 27. Re1 Bg7 28. b3 Rb8 29. Nb2 Kf8 30. Nc4 Qc7 31. f6 Bxf6 32. Bxf6 Rxf6 33. Qh8+ Ke7 34. Qg7+ { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0


